Two teenage boys were critically wounded after a hand grenade went off at a house in Vanguard Estate. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating after a hand grenade went off at a house in Vanguard Estate and critically wounded two teenage boys.Three others were also hurt in Monday night s explosion.The police s Frederick van Wyk says: The young males were rushed to various hospitals in serious conditions for emergency medical treatment. It is unknown where they got the device from. We ve opened an unlawful possession of explosives to cause injuries to persons or damage to property case for further investigation. Meanwhile, a man has been arrested for the possession of an imitation firearm and a knife in Parkwood, while another man was arrested in Lavender Hill for the illegal possession of a rifle.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)